comments: Huerter (ATL) places a hand on Jackson (LAC) as he drives to the basket and the contact is marginal.  He then establishes himself in a legal guarding position as he contests the shot attempt.
Coffey (LAC) places a hand/arm to the front of Young (ATL) during his drive to the basket and the contact is marginal.
Kennard (LAC) places a marginal hand on Gallinari's (ATL) body as he fades away during the jump shot attempt.
Zubac (LAC) briefly grasps Gallinari's (ATL) arm as he establishes position in the post and the contact is marginal.
Gallinari's (ATL) arm is not in a vertical position, but the contact with Zubac's (LAC) non-shooting arm is marginal and does not affect his shot attempt in the post.

Batum (LAC) establishes himself in a defensive position outside of the restricted area during Hunter's (ATL) driving shot attempt, but Hunter does not drive through him and dislodge him from his position.  The contact is marginal as Batum attempts to draw the charge.
Capela (ATL) legally contests Jackson's (LAC) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Hunter (ATL) places an arm at Zubac's (LAC) side, but Zubac begins to lose his balance when he backs into Hunter and is unable to get to the long rebound as he reaches backwards.
Coffey (LAC) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
Young (ATL) grazes Batum's (LAC) midsection during the jump shot attempt and the contact is marginal.
Capela (ATL) legally contests Jackson's (LAC) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Jackson (LAC) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
